      "content": {
        "parts": [
          {
            "text": "Several clinics in and around Katy, Texas, offer PRP therapy for hair loss. Here are a few options:\n\n*   **4Ever Young Anti-aging Clinic and Medical Spa**: They offer a combination treatment of PRP therapy with HydraFacial Keravive to stimulate hair growth and nourish the scalp.\n*   **Luminous MediSpa**: They offer PRP hair restoration treatments designed to rejuvenate and stimulate hair growth.\n*   **Integrative Primary Care**: Dr. Syed Farhat Zaidi uses PRP therapy to increase blood supply to hair follicles, promoting new hair growth and preventing further hair loss.\n*   **Ageless Med Spa**: They provide hair restoration treatments with PRP therapy.\n*   **The Nikko Cosmetic Surgery Center (Houston, TX)**: Dr. Anthony Nikko offers Eclipse PRP therapy for patients with thinning hair and minor bald spots and after hair restoration surgery.\n*   **CLS Health (Houston Galleria)**: Maysoon Hamed, MD, offers PRP treatments for hair restoration.\n\nThe cost of PRP for hair loss can vary. The average cost ranges from $1,500 to $3,500 for the initial 3-4 treatments. Maintenance sessions are recommended every 6-12 months and cost around $500 to $1000 per session. Skin N' Tox Aesthetics offers PRP hair treatment for $2,700 for the first 3 sessions. Village Dermatology in Houston offers PRP for hair loss for $3200 for 4 treatments, then $600 per maintenance treatment. Individual sessions for the scalp range from $400 to $1500.\n\n"
          }
        ],
